-- Soros Says Gold No Longer Haven After Euro Crisis, SCMP Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2013-04-08T12:53:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-08/soros-says-gold-no-longer-haven-after-euro-crisis-scmp-says.html
Gold has ceased to be the haven for
investors after the precious metal fell when the euro was close
to collapse last year, billionaire investor  George Soros  said in
an interview with the  South China Morning Post .  Soros, founder of the Quantum Fund, told the Post that gold
won’t decline as central banks will continue to buy the precious
metal. Still, the price will be very volatile from day to day if
there’s the prospect of a crisis, with no longer-term trend, he
said, according to a transcript of the interview posted on the
newspaper’s website today.  Gold has fallen 5.8 percent this year to $1,577.80 an ounce
at  The bullion averaged a record $1,669 last year.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
